question-1.title: What are the key advantages of financing vs. renting?
question-1.description:
ONE LOW FIXED MONTHLY PAYMENT

Monthly rental rates on a full set of automatic tools is typically $500 per month or more. Through LEVEL5 financing, you can own the same tools at a fraction of the monthly cost. In addition, at the end of your financing term, there is no balloon payment or any other hidden charges. The tools are yours.

‍ALL THE SAME BENEFITS OF OWNERSHIP‍

During your financing term, you have all of the rights and privileges of full ownership, including full coverage by the LEVEL5 warranty, access to after-sales service and technical support, product training, etc. Know that LEVEL5 offers an industry-leading 7-year, no hassle warranty on all of its automatic drywall finishing tools. This means the manufacturing workmanship of your tools will be backed by us for many years beyond the expiry of your contract. 

MORE FINANCIAL CONTROL‍

Cash is the lifeblood of any business. So why use it up purchasing capital assets (including tools)? You are able to conserve your business savings and bank lines of credit for other important expenditures that will help you to support and grow your business (such as a new truck or trailer).

MONTHLY PAYMENTS ARE TAX DEDUCTIBLE

Talk to your accountant. The interest on your financing payments can typically be deducted as business expenses on your tax return, reducing the net cost of your financing. Tax deductions are one of the biggest advantages of small equipment financing. 

DEVELOP A CREDIT PARTNERSHIP WITH LEVEL5

We’re here to support your success. financing partnership, you have an opportunity to build a strong, prosperous credit relationship with LEVEL5 and our financing partners. We can continue to fund your tooling needs in the future as you grow and thrive.

question-2.title: How much will my monthly payment be?
question-2.description:
The calculation of your monthly payment amount is a function of three variables:

  1. The configuration of the toolset you require and its cost;
  2. The term of the financing that you choose;
  3. Your credit history.

Your credit score is not affected when you submit an initial application. Why not apply and see what is offered by our financing partner? There is no obligation and the final decision to accept the loan terms is yours.

question-3.title: What is the interest rate for my financing?
question-3.description: Interest rates on unsecured small equipment capital financings is highly variable, but the algorithm is primarily influenced by your credit record and the term of the financing that you choose. The rates can be as low as 4% per annum.

question-4.title: Is there a balloon payment at the end of the financing term?
question-4.description:
There is no balloon payment or any other hidden fees at the end of your financing term. 

Know that LEVEL5 offers an industry-leading 7-year, no hassle warranty on all of its automatic drywall finishing tools. This means the manufacturing workmanship of your tools will be backed by us for many years beyond the expiry of your contract.

question-5.title: Can I payoff my financing early?
question-5.description: Yes! A loan with our financing partner Credit Key includes flexible payment terms. If you pay off the balance in full early, any future interest that would have been due for the remaining months of the loan is avoided. Also, there are no penalties or fees for early repayment.
